Gets the SQL state code from the supplied {@link SQLException exception}._

Some JDBC drivers nest the actual exception from a batched update, so we_might need to dig down into the nested exception._@param ex the exception from which the {@link SQLException#getSQLState() SQL state}_is to be extracted_@return the SQL state code
codeText: private String getSqlState(SQLException ex) {_		String sqlState = ex.getSQLState()__		if (sqlState == null) {_			SQLException nestedEx = ex.getNextException()__			if (nestedEx != null) {_				sqlState = nestedEx.getSQLState()__			}_		}_		return sqlState__	}
